task.name: Receives store orders
task.documentation:
SCM_12

When returned devices arrive at the PDC, a CTDI employee will visually inspect packaging of every shipment for signs of tampering. If CTDI sees evidence of package tampering, the manager initiates a dispute process to notify CCI Supply Chain via SCM IT Help Ticket to further investigate issue and/or file insurance claim with Assurion and contact the carrier.

task.name: Order is picked, verified, and packed for shipment
task.documentation:
SCM_04 

CTDI to ensure warehouse is under 24/7 camera surveillance. Cameras must monitor dock, grounds, access points, and cages. 

SCM_05

CTDI will perform a first quality check om 100% of wireless inventory shipments prior to shipping. Every time a quality check is performed, the CTDI employee performing the quality check logs their name, date, time, and result of the quality check in a log. 

SCM_06 

A separate CTDI employee will perform a second quality check by randomly selecting a sample of shipments. Every time a quality check is performed, the CTDI employee performing the quality checks logs their name, date, time and result of the quality check in a log. 

SCM_08

Access to wireless inventory storage and shipping doc is limited to authorized personnel designated by the floor manager. 

SCM_10

Boxes containing wireless inventory are not designated with any Cox logos at either the PDC or retail store to prevent theft of devices in transit.
